@NODE INTR "Introduction"

Thankyou downloading/buying this program. Its very useful. Yes. Oooh where 
to  start. Okay, lets go back, way back to say, oh a couple of days ago... oh 
forget it, just read the @{"history" LINK HIST}.


Seriously now then. You`re probably (not) wondering why I wrote this
program. Well, I wrote it because I couldn`t be bothered to pay some money
to a PD library to get a HD password protection program and I couldn`t
find one on Aminet so I wrote one myself, as you do.

So thats what HDP is. A Hard Drive Protector. But not just any Hd
protector etc..

I can`t be bothered to write any more of this intro so just skip along to
the @{"Requirements" LINK REQU} section.

@ENDNODE


@NODE REQU "Requirements."

Well, young lad/lass, you will need:
====================================
* An Amiga.
* A TV/Monitor.
* A PSU.
* A Mouse.
* A Mouse Mat
* A head, equipped with eyes, nose, mouth, and brain (brain optional).
* Fifty tonnes of potasssium chloride.
* And a Hard drive.
    

It should work on ALL AMIGAs.
Now go to @{"Useage" LINK USEA}
@ENDNODE


@NODE USEA "Useage"

			Installation  &  Useage
                       =========================


Right. This is the rum olde bit of the guide where you have to pay lots of
attention. PLEASE Pay Attention! This is very important and I`m not joking
for once.

In your S:Startup-Sequence file type this right at the beginning:

ASSIGN HDP: DH0:HDP
HDP:HDP.MAIN

This is of course assuming that the HDP drawer is in the partition DH0: so
if the drawer ISN`T in DH0: then type in the partition that it IS in.
And then save it.


Reboot, and you should then get a screen with a few windows in it. This
will disappear and you should be asked for a new password. Make one up
(this is the bit where your brain comes in)  and REMEMBER IT. WRITE IT
DOWN SOMEWHERE. I WILL NOT BE HELD RESPONSIBLE IF YOU FORGET YOUR PASSWORD
AND CAN`T GET INTO YOUR HARD DRIVE AGAIN.  Press enter and then you will
be asked for the password. Type in the one that you just made up. Then
after a few secs Workbench should appear! Hurrah!  Now every time you
reboot you will be asked for the password.

When you are in workbench you can change the password again if you want.
Just click on "HDP.PREFS" and you can change it.  And oh yeah if you want
you could run the program in the other partitions startup-sequences! 
But if you want a different password for each one you need to: @{"REGISTER!!" LINK REGI}
Okay? Now go to @{"Bugs" LINK BUGS}
@ENDNODE


@NODE BUGS "Known Bugs"

			Known Bugs
                       ============

There are no known bugs (maybe just a couple of spiders, ho ho).
Actually there IS one but its very unlikely to happen. Sometimes the
file where the password is kept may go all funny. You`ll know if this has
happened cos the password won`t work. Ahem.
If that happens then contact me, it can be easily solved because I know
how to solve it..

By the way, If you take a peek at the password file and you can see the
password, don`t worry, after the program has been used for a while, this
password should turn into binary, so prying eyes won`t be able to find it
out.  No I don`t mean that when you enter the password, you`ll have to
type in binary, cos your actual password will still stay the same. Clever
huh! 

Now go to @{"REGISTRATION!!" LINK REGI}
@ENDNODE


